Pre-Game Insights: Aaron Nola will take the mound for the Phillies in their season finale against the Nationals on Sunday.
Aaron Nola has a 13-8 record and a 3.52 ERA, while Jake Irvin has a 10-13 record and a 4.22 ERA.
The Phillies are still in contention for the top seed in the National League, which adds motivation for the game.
The Nationals have struggled this season and are looking to end on a high note.
